HEADWORD: Inogen
<hw>In"o*gen</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <grk>'i`s</grk>,
<grk>'ino`s</grk>, a muscle + <ets>-gen</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>A complex nitrogenous substance, which, by
Hermann's hypothesis, is continually decomposed and reproduced in the
muscles, during their life.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inoperation</ent>⟦br⟧
